Text.Value: What's it now?
The shop. The bloody shop. Thing was like a noose around my neck, getting tighter every day.
I don't have much now. But a bit of peace is worth an awful lot.
Whatever you say.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a little bit of humor. Player is being mean to her but she's not taking the bait.

Text.Value: It's yours.
Give Derryth the noblestalk.
You might lighten up on Baelen. He seems harmless enough.
Huh! Now there's a mug I won't soon forget.
We both of us deserved better than life gave us. Now he's off in the City of Judgement, probably wasting away unclaimed, the old heathen. And I'm here. Alone.
Leave.
I wish you both the best.
Look who it is! You're just in time - noblestalk's propagated a treat. Have a look.
Take your pick.
The place is in shambles, to be honest. But Walrus softens the blow.
I owe you a debt of gratitude, believe it or not. When you healed my husband, Baelen, I thought my life was over. Turns out it was just beginning.
Bah! No it isn't. I'll call him... Walrus.
You... but... how?! Well... never mind how. Listen here: if you give me that mushroom, I'll propagate it to the Hells and back.
We've even enough left over to keep ourselves fed. Not that Baelen's worth the gold it takes to keep him fattened up.

EditorData.NodeContext: She's unpleasant but she is glad to see you, in her way.

Text.Value: Hey, you. Take a look at this cat. Does he look like a 'Harry' to you?
Leave.
Well, what is it?
Leave.
Go on, then.
What will you do now that you're done with the shop?
You don't realise how much your life is choking you until you can breathe again.
Maybe I'll get to courting after a little while. Then again, maybe I'll just get a cat.
I'd like to give you that noblestalk.
I met him in your shop. He seems to be doing well.
You know what? So am I. And I hope Baelen finds his peace while he still can, too.
I'll give you a discount on everything here, and... well... you'll be keeping food in my mouth and a roof over my head for months.
Baelen made my life hell. And when I had the chance to return the favour, I took it. That's no way to live. Now we're both free.
I admit, I was worried about the two of you.
Get on with it.
As it happens, I already have some noblestalk to hand.
I'd like to trade.
He's wrecking my head, as always. Makes himself useful with a broom from time to time, at least.
Livens the place up, doesn't he? Yes he does, indeed he does!

EditorData.NodeContext: First bit to the player, second to the cat on the ground.

Text.Value: You don't know him like I do. He may play the lamb, but beneath it all, he's a black-hearted ogre. I got the scars to prove it.
Anyway. We can knock a little off the top if you've a mind to buy.

EditorData.NodeContext: She's unpleasant but she is glad to see you, in her way.

Text.Value: I ain't a beggar. But. Please.

EditorData.NodeContext: A hard woman softening out of necessity.

Text.Value: Anyway. You ought to keep your nose in your own corner. You might upset folk.
Bonecloak's. Get what you can before we have to shutter the place.

EditorData.logicalname: Not met in UND - Baelen alive - Didn't give shroom in UND

Text.Value: Just fine, now Walrus is here to keep me company. Isn't that right, precious?
Cat's crabs, you've saved my arse. Come back tomorrow, hey? There'll be more of the stuff already. Grows like a weed in the right hands. And erm. Thank you. Very much.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hardness returned to her, but she's happy now

Text.Value: Noblestalk is why the customers came. We were out on our arses soon enough without it. Too bad my worthless fella couldn't get one simple thing right in his life.
You could've done me a great turn with that noblestalk. It's what attracted the customers. Won't be able to keep the candles lit without it. Hope that pleases you.
What can I do you for?

EditorData.logicalname: Hasmet - Not met in UND - Baelen alive - Didn't give shroom in UND

Text.Value: It's nice to see a familiar face. After living a handsbreadth away from Baelen most of my life, I've forgotten how to be alone.
Oh. It's you.

EditorData.NodeContext: She's unpleasant but she is glad to see you, in her way.

Text.Value: Well, what is it?
Hope you're here to buy something.
Huh. It's you. I never forget a face.
Turns out I didn't hate life. I hated that life.

EditorData.NodeContext: She breathes in deeply through her nose, a sigh of contentment

Text.Value: Gee, thanks. Looks like you grew a conscience after all.

EditorData.NodeContext: She's grateful but also annoyed with the player.

Text.Value: When he got sick, I was grateful for the relief. But so angry, too.
Maybe. But if you ever find yourself down on your luck, I hope you'll receive the same kindness I'm asking for now.
This'll help. I'll be able to propagate a fair few from this one, too. Come back another day and I may have some for you. At a fair price.
How are you getting along without Baelen?
Sorry, this noblestalk is mine.
Get what you can while the getting's good. We'll be closing our doors soon enough.

EditorData.logicalname: Baelen dead, not met, not met in UND

Text.Value: Well! Aren't you a sight for sore eyes? Made it out of the Underdark in one piece, I see.

EditorData.NodeContext: More jovial than usual. She's doing well.

Text.Value: I'd like to trade.
I'd like to trade.
Sure I did. Before he could do me any worse damage than he did for the first seventy years of our marriage.
You take care now, all right? Be sure you do. Life's too short not to.
I know you. So you made it out of the Underdark. More'n I can say for Baelen.
You get your wares from the Underdark?
Thank you. Baelen won't agree with me, but I say we both deserve it.
How about '[GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53]'?
Are you glad to be back in Baldur's Gate?
Leave.
But it brought no relief. Not really. So when you turned him back, I turned mine.
Happy as a pig in shit, I'm sure. Eighty years we've been married. Seventy of 'em, he was a mean, violent man who loved nothing but the drink.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a scoff, bitterness in her voice.

Text.Value: That's a great name.
We mostly trade in noblestalk, and my fool of a fella Baelen never came back with any.
Him losing his mind softened him and hardened me. I hated him so much - more than I knew a person could carry. And now I wasn't too scared to show it.
Welcome to Bonecloak's. Doors are still open thanks to that noblestalk you helped us with.

EditorData.NodeContext: She's unpleasant but she is glad to see you, in her way.

Text.Value: Well. It's a lot quieter without him bumbling about the place. He was on the slow fade out anyway.
It's the least you could do.
The two of you deserve each other.
Glad to see you're doing well.
Couldn't be more delighted.
Please. It's a cat, not a clown. But he's no 'Harry' either, is he? I think I'll call him... Walrus.
How are you and Baelen getting on?
Only place to find our best-seller. Noblestalk's this place's bread and butter - milk and eggs, too. Without it, we're sunk.
If the old sack was going to die, he could've brought back some noblestalk beforehand. Without the bloody fungus, Bonecloak's days are numbered.
So he got well, and you left him?
Oh, sure. Cultists on the loose, a murderer hacking people to bits, and big metal freaks stomping hither, thither, and yon.
That noblestalk you gave me helped, though. It's what keeps the customers coming. Bloody fungus is all that keeps our candles lit.
I don't care what you name your cat.
You should've been. Baelen was an awful, violent man. Would've killed me if I stayed. And truth be told, if you hadn't healed him, I might've done the same to him.
I'd like to trade.
Had to be practical about it. Slip out while he slept. I knew if I stayed there, it'd be the death of me.
If you came for noblestalk, you're out of luck. Last trip to the Underdark was a miserable failure. Won't be able to keep the lamps lit much longer.
You sound like a beggar to me.
Well. You've every right to it. If you see me on the streets in future, throw me a copper or two, eh?
How's that noblestalk treating you, eh? Better be good. 'Shroom's why our customers came. We're out on our arses soon enough without it, I hope you know.
He was a terror most of his life, you know. Mean. Drunk. Got a few scars I could show you that'd make you wince.
Suit yourself. Me and... Walrus - that suits you, doesn't it, you lovely thing? - don't need your help anyhow.
Huh! Now there's a mug I won't soon forget.

Synopsis: The player talks to Derryth after she returns from the Underdark, with or without the Noblestalk.
